Help for xOP:

The xOP commands allow you to maintain channel
access lists.  Users on the VOP list will be
automatically set +v in the channel.  Users on
the AOP list will be automatically set +o on the
channel.  Users on the SOP list will be
automatically set +o on the channel and be allowed
to add users to the VOP and AOP lists.

You may also specify a hostmask (nick!user@host)
for the VOP and AOP lists.

Not all channel access entries can be edited
with these commands, see the FLAGS and FORCEXOP
help entries for details. Note that use of
FORCEXOP can destroy a lot of information.

Syntax: VOP|HOP|AOP|SOP <#channel> ADD|DEL|LIST <nickname|hostmask>

Examples:
    /msg &nick& VOP #foo ADD bar
    /msg &nick& VOP #foo ADD foo!*@bar.com
    /msg &nick& AOP #foo DEL bar
    /msg &nick& SOP #foo LIST
